Volunteers shall not be considered employees of the board or the Commonwealth of Kentucky; however, they shall be granted:
An allowance which, at a minimum, shall equal the federal minimum wage;
Appeal rights pursuant to the provisions of KRS 154.1-740;
Relocation benefits;
Health benefits;
Social security benefits;
Free tuition for one full-time semester at a state-supported Kentucky college or university for every twelve (12) months' service completed in the corps; and
Workers' compensation.

Notwithstanding other provisions of the Kentucky Revised Statutes, volunteers shall not be eligible to receive:
Dental benefits;
Disability insurance;
Life insurance;
Reimbursement for meals; or
Unemployment insurance.
